    "narrative": "The LawDog lineup for April 29th is anchored by two high-upside outfielders who are poised to exploit favorable conditions. **Lawrence Butler** carries the day\u2019s highest projection (73.43), benefiting from a significant 10% park boost and a soft matchup against Michael Wacha. Paired with **Daulton Varsho** (70.72), who enjoys an excellent platoon advantage against Nick Pivetta/Bello and a 13% skill-based boost, these two represent our primary engine for counting stats. **Jonathan Aranda** also stands out as an elite play; despite a standard projection, the 12% platoon edge against Graham Ashcraft makes him a high-efficiency target at 1B, while **Cal Raleigh** remains a constant threat, leveraged here by an aggressive #2 spot in the order that maximizes his rbi and run potential.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the optimizer today involved the marginal range, specifically keeping **Masyn Winn** and **Matt Chapman** active while moving **Luis Arraez** to the bench. **Masyn Winn** remains in the lineup to hunt for stolen bases\u2014our most critical scarcity category\u2014despite a neutral score of 41.17, as his speed profile provides utility that the pure floor of **Luis Arraez** (40.28) lacks. **Matt Chapman** clears the 40.0 threshold by a hair at 42.56, though he is on thin ice; he and **Bryson Stott** (51.79) are both tethered to a 40% rain risk, which could dampen their output or result in shortened appearances. We are keeping a close watch on **Masyn Winn** and **Lawrence Butler**, whose scores are currently based on pending lineup assumptions; should they slide down the order, those efficiency numbers will likely crater toward our benched cohort, including **Gleyber Torres** and **Jung Hoo Lee**, who currently sit below the 40.0 efficiency floor.",
